00:00:22,300 --> 00:00:26,233
(What's Wrong With Secretary Kim?)

7
00:00:27,233 --> 00:00:28,720
What would you know?

8
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:30,333
You know nothing about love.

9
00:00:32,766 --> 00:00:35,020
Then do you, Ms. Kim?

10
00:00:35,100 --> 00:00:36,233
When you've been
single all your life.

11
00:00:38,300 --> 00:00:40,786
I've read about it in books,
you know!

12
00:00:40,866 --> 00:00:42,266
Good for you.

13
00:00:42,966 --> 00:00:44,700
Ah, the water's boiling.

14
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:52,000
Why is Thank-cow
facing down like that?

15
00:00:54,533 --> 00:00:55,286
No, not there!

16
00:00:55,366 --> 00:00:56,700
Not over there!

17
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:30,600
A little longer.

18
00:01:32,633 --> 00:01:34,466
Just a little longer.

19
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:44,766
I thought maybe
I should try this love thing.

20
00:01:48,566 --> 00:01:49,700
With you.

21
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:20,486
...Said that childish book
over there.

22
00:02:20,566 --> 00:02:22,100
Is this what they call 'romance?'

23
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:25,933
Oh...

24
00:02:28,333 --> 00:02:30,353
You memorized the whole book
in that short time?

25
00:02:30,433 --> 00:02:33,500
Your memory surprises me
every time.

26
00:02:41,066 --> 00:02:42,220
Um...

27
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:44,233
Is that water still boiling?

28
00:03:10,866 --> 00:03:12,800
- Help yourself.
- Ah.

29
00:03:15,300 --> 00:03:17,386
My principle is not really
eating MSG and

30
00:03:17,466 --> 00:03:18,653
other chemical additives,

31
00:03:18,733 --> 00:03:20,933
but since you went to the effort,
I will eat it this time only.

32
00:03:21,833 --> 00:03:23,433
Yes, it'll be my honor.

33
00:03:33,266 --> 00:03:34,333
How is it?

34
00:03:36,533 --> 00:03:37,453
Not bad.

35
00:03:37,533 --> 00:03:38,766
Really?

36
00:03:48,166 --> 00:03:52,066
Oh, ramen is best with
some kimchi.

37
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:54,820
Sodium and sodium?

38
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:56,966
Does that make sense,
in terms of nutrition?

39
00:04:34,566 --> 00:04:36,420
Thanks for the ramen today.

40
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:37,286
Right.

41
00:04:37,366 --> 00:04:38,986
After calling it a bowl of MSG,

42
00:04:39,066 --> 00:04:41,220
you downed the whole thing!

43
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:45,086
Because it was my first time
having you cook for me.

44
00:04:45,166 --> 00:04:46,400
Was it?

45
00:04:47,900 --> 00:04:50,120
Oh, make sure to
disinfect your cut.

46
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:51,966
and apply some ointment
before going to bed.

47
00:04:53,033 --> 00:04:54,000
Alright.

48
00:05:08,833 --> 00:05:09,933
Thank you...

49
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:12,766
...For today.

50
00:05:35,466 --> 00:05:38,233
(Episode 5)

51
00:05:46,933 --> 00:05:48,520
Now that he mentioned it,
that really was a first.

52
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:50,433
To have him in here.

53
00:05:55,033 --> 00:05:56,133
Mr. Lee?

54
00:05:57,133 --> 00:05:59,333
Hmmm? But he didn't
forget anything.

55
00:06:03,033 --> 00:06:04,020
Oh!

56
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:06,086
Ta-da!

57
00:06:06,166 --> 00:06:07,200
Sis.

58
00:06:07,733 --> 00:06:09,320
Hey, what brings you here?

59
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:10,720
What, can't I?

60
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,886
Or do I have to
make an appointment?

61
00:06:12,966 --> 00:06:13,920
Oh.

62
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,753
Here. You've got beer, right?

63
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:16,933
Yeah.

64
00:06:19,633 --> 00:06:20,653
Oh what?

65
00:06:20,733 --> 00:06:22,520
Was someone here?

66
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:24,233
Huh? What?

67
00:06:27,033 --> 00:06:27,853
Oh...

68
00:06:27,933 --> 00:06:29,553
Just Mr. Lee.

69
00:06:29,633 --> 00:06:32,586
Oh my goodness! You must be crazy!

70
00:06:32,666 --> 00:06:35,120
You let a man inside your house?

71
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:37,686
No, he was only
staying for some ramen.

72
00:06:37,766 --> 00:06:39,233
What? Ramen?

73
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:43,300
Not some other noodles, but ramen?

74
00:06:44,366 --> 00:06:47,120
What, is there something
so special about ramen?

75
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:48,786
Of course!

76
00:06:48,866 --> 00:06:54,353
When a girl says,
'Oppa, you want to stay for ramen,'

77
00:06:54,433 --> 00:06:57,953
she means, 'After you finish that,
we're now dating.'

78
00:06:58,033 --> 00:06:59,320
That's what it means!

79
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:01,653
In other words, 'I like you!'

80
00:07:01,733 --> 00:07:03,920
What, not even caviar or truffles,

81
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:07,820
but just instant food that's
bombarded with MSG?

82
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:09,786
Asking to stay for that
had such a deep connotation?

83
00:07:09,866 --> 00:07:11,853
God, you're so naive!

84
00:07:11,933 --> 00:07:13,586
The ramen's just an excuse.

85
00:07:13,666 --> 00:07:16,820
Put a man and a woman in
an enclosed space,

86
00:07:16,900 --> 00:07:18,800
and they'll eventually
want to hold hands.

87
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:22,733
And hug, and...

88
00:07:25,866 --> 00:07:28,233
- Why, what is it?
- Huh? It's nothing...

89
00:07:30,833 --> 00:07:32,620
Is this perhaps about you
and Ms. Kim?

90
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:34,420
Just what are you...

91
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:36,033
You think we've got
that much free time?

92
00:07:38,366 --> 00:07:40,133
This is about my cousin's
friend from his college.

93
00:07:41,966 --> 00:07:43,320
Then do I look like I've got
too much free time?

94
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:46,933
To listen to your cousin's
friend from college's story?

95
00:07:54,266 --> 00:07:55,586
Hey.

96
00:07:55,666 --> 00:07:57,653
You like Mr. Lee, don't you?

97
00:07:57,733 --> 00:07:59,253
No way!

98
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:01,033
Hey, what is with that?

99
00:08:04,133 --> 00:08:04,986
Mi-so,

100
00:08:05,066 --> 00:08:06,420
let me tell you something.

101
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:09,100
You need to date
your own kind to be happy.

102
00:08:10,433 --> 00:08:14,686
This doesn't apply to just humans,
but to all living things!

103
00:08:14,766 --> 00:08:16,920
Did you ever see that
dog and the bird

104
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:20,653
that are always together,
on 'What in the World?'

105
00:08:20,733 --> 00:08:22,066
Dog-bird...

106
00:08:26,233 --> 00:08:28,786
I wasn't trying to swear.

107
00:08:28,866 --> 00:08:30,820
So you're saying that
this dog and a bird are together.

108
00:08:30,900 --> 00:08:33,486
Yes. It weirds you out too,
doesn't it?

109
00:08:33,566 --> 00:08:36,586
Just makes you say,
'What in the world,' huh?

110
00:08:36,666 --> 00:08:38,220
Well, that's what this is.

111
00:08:38,300 --> 00:08:40,466
Two different kinds,
trying to be a couple.

112
00:08:41,366 --> 00:08:45,653
What, are you saying Mr. Lee is
a dog, and I'm a bird?

113
00:08:45,733 --> 00:08:47,120
Kind of.

114
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:50,520
Because he's a chaebol
while we're average citizens.

115
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:52,100
You're two different kinds.

116
00:08:55,633 --> 00:08:56,986
I mean,

117
00:08:57,066 --> 00:09:00,786
if you were to tell him about how
we always fought over the drumstick

118
00:09:00,866 --> 00:09:03,553
do you think
he'll ever understand? Huh?

119
00:09:03,633 --> 00:09:04,686
I mean, over a drumstick,

120
00:09:04,766 --> 00:09:07,500
and not over some stock share!

121
00:09:10,133 --> 00:09:13,220
In other words,
he's from a different galaxy.

122
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:16,366
A galaxy with
a distance you can't close in.

123
00:09:25,766 --> 00:09:28,353
You know I'm saying this
because I'm worried about you, right?

124
00:09:28,433 --> 00:09:31,266
In case you'll only
end up hurt later.

125
00:09:33,766 --> 00:09:35,400
I know.

126
00:09:36,166 --> 00:09:37,333
But...

127
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:40,333
This is my problem.

128
00:09:59,233 --> 00:10:00,253
Take care.

129
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:01,886
Text me once you get home.

130
00:10:01,966 --> 00:10:05,086
Alright, I'll get going.
I'll leave you to get some rest.

131
00:10:05,166 --> 00:10:06,266
Bye.

132
00:10:12,300 --> 00:10:14,066
Ha... I don't have
a good feeling about this.

133
00:10:43,633 --> 00:10:45,420
Mom!

134
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:48,166
Mom! Dad!

135
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:51,953
Where are you?

136
00:10:52,033 --> 00:10:53,766
I'm so scared...

137
00:10:54,866 --> 00:10:57,133
So scared...

138
00:11:27,033 --> 00:11:28,166
(Mr. Lee)

139
00:11:28,666 --> 00:11:29,553
Yes, Mr. Lee.

140
00:11:29,633 --> 00:11:31,253
Where are you?

141
00:11:31,333 --> 00:11:33,486
I'm still at home, did you need...

142
00:11:33,566 --> 00:11:35,253
Are you ready to
come into work?

143
00:11:35,333 --> 00:11:37,320
Yes, I was just about to step out.

144
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:38,953
Then make it quick.

145
00:11:39,033 --> 00:11:40,766
Yes, sir. Uh... what?

146
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:43,300
What?

147
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,966
Oh my, why are you...

148
00:11:51,033 --> 00:11:53,133
I'll be right out, then.

149
00:12:00,300 --> 00:12:01,520
What brings you here
so early in the morning?

150
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:03,166
Oh my God!

151
00:12:30,700 --> 00:12:31,800
I'm so sorry.

152
00:12:36,666 --> 00:12:39,266
- No need to be sorry.
- Sorry?

153
00:12:40,466 --> 00:12:41,766
- What?
- Sorry?

154
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,086
Oh...

155
00:12:45,166 --> 00:12:46,200
Oh, I see.

156
00:12:52,166 --> 00:12:53,366
Ms. Kim, where are you going?

157
00:12:54,733 --> 00:12:57,553
To the driver's seat.
Since Mr. Yang isn't here...

158
00:12:57,633 --> 00:12:59,266
No, I'll do the driving.

159
00:13:00,466 --> 00:13:01,766
Sorry?

160
00:13:03,666 --> 00:13:04,933
Get in, Ms. Kim.

161
00:13:20,566 --> 00:13:21,566
Watch your head.

162
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:34,033
You look pretty today...

163
00:13:38,666 --> 00:13:40,253
...Is what you want to hear,

164
00:13:40,333 --> 00:13:42,853
then I suggest you pay
more attention to your fashion.

165
00:13:42,933 --> 00:13:44,220
- Sorry?
- That blouse.

166
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:46,520
You wore that
last Wednesday and Friday.

167
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:49,200
Someone might mistake it for
our company's uniform.

168
00:13:50,900 --> 00:13:55,053
Wednesday, and Friday...

169
00:13:55,133 --> 00:13:57,086
How do you remember all that?

170
00:13:57,166 --> 00:13:58,286
It pains me, too.

171
00:13:58,366 --> 00:14:00,153
This great memory of mine.

172
00:14:00,233 --> 00:14:02,933
See, sometimes I'd rather
forget some things, you know?

173
00:14:08,566 --> 00:14:09,600
Here.

174
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:16,853
What's this?

175
00:14:16,933 --> 00:14:18,986
Croque Monsieur, made by our chef.

176
00:14:19,066 --> 00:14:21,120
You may have it if you want,
if you haven't had breakfast.

177
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:23,000
Oh, thank you.

178
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:32,966
You may also drink that coffee.

179
00:14:35,766 --> 00:14:37,820
- Alright.
- Oh, and that shopping bag!

180
00:14:37,900 --> 00:14:39,566
- You may also have it, too.
- Sorry?

181
00:14:43,433 --> 00:14:44,733
Thank you.

182
00:14:49,166 --> 00:14:50,500
What, now?

183
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:05,200
Let's go, then.

184
00:15:38,166 --> 00:15:40,953
Me first?

185
00:15:41,033 --> 00:15:42,333
Yes.

186
00:16:20,700 --> 00:16:22,853
Young-ok, how do I look?

187
00:16:22,933 --> 00:16:24,620
I got a new BB cream!

188
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:25,753
Tsk, sweetie.

189
00:16:25,833 --> 00:16:27,853
Rub your eyes before
you rub that BB cream on.

190
00:16:27,933 --> 00:16:30,220
You have sleep in your eyes.

191
00:16:30,300 --> 00:16:33,233
When did that...

192
00:16:34,966 --> 00:16:36,166
Oh, you scared me!

193
00:16:36,666 --> 00:16:37,853
From 10 minutes ago.

194
00:16:37,933 --> 00:16:41,166
Why are you only
telling me this now? Ugh.

195
00:16:44,633 --> 00:16:45,933
Good morning, sir.

196
00:16:47,433 --> 00:16:48,733
Good morning.

197
00:16:53,466 --> 00:16:54,486
'Good morning?'

198
00:16:54,566 --> 00:16:57,153
What, isn't this the first time
Mr. Lee greeted us...

199
00:16:57,233 --> 00:16:58,686
- ...So gently?
- No.

200
00:16:58,766 --> 00:17:00,220
He was always nice to me.

201
00:17:00,300 --> 00:17:01,586
Oh, really?

202
00:17:01,666 --> 00:17:02,320
Then why not me?

203
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:04,120
Are you sure you weren't
dreaming, Ms. Bong?

204
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:05,753
Hey, come on!

205
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:08,600
By the way, did something
good happen to Mr. Lee?

206
00:17:11,066 --> 00:17:12,886
Well... who knows?

207
00:17:12,966 --> 00:17:14,920
Who knows?

208
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:16,520
Alright, let's start!

209
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:17,886
- Alright.
- Thank you for this.

210
00:17:17,966 --> 00:17:19,353
Ms. Bong, have some of this
and come to your senses.

211
00:17:19,433 --> 00:17:21,766
- Alright, you can stop.
- Thank you!

212
00:17:22,533 --> 00:17:23,966
Don't give me
something you've been eating.

213
00:17:32,766 --> 00:17:35,053
Young-joon, you perfect man!

214
00:17:35,133 --> 00:17:37,286
Not only are your looks perfect,

215
00:17:37,366 --> 00:17:40,433
but you have a warm heart that
knows how to love.

216
00:17:53,666 --> 00:17:56,733
Mr. Lee? How about we apply that
ointment again on your cut?

217
00:18:23,466 --> 00:18:24,966
Or would you
rather do it yourself?

218
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:29,366
You can just keep going...

219
00:18:31,966 --> 00:18:33,986
Oh, did you already go over
our next quarter's plans?

220
00:18:34,066 --> 00:18:36,366
I'll tidy them... ouch!

221
00:18:37,466 --> 00:18:38,720
Are you alright?

222
00:18:38,800 --> 00:18:40,300
I'm alright.

223
00:18:45,300 --> 00:18:46,600
I can do it myself.

224
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:51,466
This is for treating my cuts.

225
00:18:53,233 --> 00:18:55,400
I'm precise with this
'give and take' thing.

226
00:19:27,766 --> 00:19:30,486
From now on, I'll have to
use tablets to check documents.

227
00:19:30,566 --> 00:19:31,486
Sorry?

228
00:19:31,566 --> 00:19:33,033
Paper is dangerous.

229
00:19:35,133 --> 00:19:37,366
Oh... Sure.

230
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:01,666
Just what is wrong with me?

231
00:20:12,133 --> 00:20:14,633
Ms. Kim? What are you doing?

232
00:20:16,666 --> 00:20:17,753
Huh?

233
00:20:17,833 --> 00:20:19,966
- What...
- That...

234
00:20:22,566 --> 00:20:23,520
Oh my!

235
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:25,633
Why is this in...

236
00:20:27,300 --> 00:20:29,333
I didn't know you made mistakes.

237
00:20:31,233 --> 00:20:33,133
- Here.
- Thank you.

238
00:21:04,666 --> 00:21:06,653
Are you alright,

239
00:21:06,733 --> 00:21:07,733
honey?

240
00:21:09,700 --> 00:21:11,420
Do you think I am?

241
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:15,686
I have just two son, and
they're worse than strangers.

242
00:21:15,766 --> 00:21:18,166
I can't take this anymore.

243
00:21:21,466 --> 00:21:25,620
Go shopping or something,
to take your mind off things.

244
00:21:25,700 --> 00:21:28,220
Yes! What was it again?
You had that purse you liked.

245
00:21:28,300 --> 00:21:30,053
That limited edition!

246
00:21:30,133 --> 00:21:32,420
Why not treat yourself?

247
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:33,420
Forget it.

248
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:36,220
Why not? It's not like you don't
have the money or elegance.

249
00:21:36,300 --> 00:21:38,953
Go and get that purse right now!

250
00:21:39,033 --> 00:21:40,053
I said, forget it.

251
00:21:40,133 --> 00:21:42,466
Hey.

252
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:47,186
Mr. Choi? Go to the
department store right now, and...

253
00:21:47,266 --> 00:21:49,153
I said, forget it!

254
00:21:49,233 --> 00:21:50,620
But how can I?

255
00:21:50,700 --> 00:21:52,153
Just go get that purse!

256
00:21:52,233 --> 00:21:53,766
I already did!

257
00:21:55,966 --> 00:21:57,586
- What?
- I got it when it hit the stores.

258
00:21:57,666 --> 00:21:59,133
Last week.

259
00:22:02,333 --> 00:22:05,200
Oh, is that right?

260
00:22:08,033 --> 00:22:09,433
Oh...

261
00:22:21,300 --> 00:22:24,253
When are you planning to
apologize to Young-joon?

262
00:22:24,333 --> 00:22:25,400
Sorry?

263
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:27,533
Well...

264
00:22:29,266 --> 00:22:32,453
Hey, your mother is
having trouble sleeping.

265
00:22:32,533 --> 00:22:36,166
Make up, so she can
get that burden off her chest.

266
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:39,253
Yes, Father. I understand.

267
00:22:39,333 --> 00:22:40,500
Hmph.

268
00:22:41,533 --> 00:22:42,920
Oh, and...

269
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:45,553
Don't interrupt Young-joon for
trivial things.

