00:38:14,866 --> 00:38:16,100
Sorry?

538
00:38:17,833 --> 00:38:19,266
Let's have a glass of wine.

539
00:38:24,200 --> 00:38:25,533
I have something to say.

540
00:38:29,233 --> 00:38:30,733
Something to say?

541
00:38:37,566 --> 00:38:38,920
Then I'll book the
Illusion Hotel lounge

542
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:41,653
that we recently acquired.

543
00:38:41,733 --> 00:38:44,020
So you can also
check it out on the way.

544
00:38:44,100 --> 00:38:44,986
No.

545
00:38:45,066 --> 00:38:48,020
I already booked elsewhere.

546
00:38:48,100 --> 00:38:49,586
Sorry?

547
00:38:49,666 --> 00:38:51,833
You made a booking yourself?

548
00:39:42,566 --> 00:39:43,686
Excuse me.

549
00:39:43,766 --> 00:39:44,833
Ah, yes.

550
00:39:45,766 --> 00:39:47,386
Can I try this on?

551
00:39:47,466 --> 00:39:48,653
Oh, sorry.

552
00:39:48,733 --> 00:39:50,666
We're out of size S.

553
00:39:51,533 --> 00:39:52,966
But you can make an order.

554
00:39:54,033 --> 00:39:56,386
It's alright, then.
I need it right now, so...

555
00:39:56,466 --> 00:39:58,120
- Oh, right now?
- Yes.

556
00:39:58,200 --> 00:40:00,400
Going on a date, are you?

557
00:40:02,766 --> 00:40:03,966
A date?

558
00:40:04,700 --> 00:40:06,866
No, it's nothing like that.

559
00:40:10,833 --> 00:40:12,300
It's okay, I can look myself.

560
00:40:24,200 --> 00:40:25,186
Yes, Morpheus.

561
00:40:25,266 --> 00:40:27,053
Are you off work?
What are you up to?

562
00:40:27,133 --> 00:40:28,986
I have an appointment, so...

563
00:40:29,066 --> 00:40:30,986
Really? Where?

564
00:40:31,066 --> 00:40:32,686
At the M Hotel Lounge.

565
00:40:32,766 --> 00:40:33,720
Hey.

566
00:40:33,800 --> 00:40:35,353
I just happened to be
around there.

567
00:40:35,433 --> 00:40:37,286
Can I see you for a second?

568
00:40:37,366 --> 00:40:39,120
Right now's a bit...

569
00:40:39,200 --> 00:40:42,020
Like I told you,
I have an appointment.

570
00:40:42,100 --> 00:40:45,153
I wanted to give you
my answer for your proposal.

571
00:40:45,233 --> 00:40:47,720
Don't blame me if I end up
changing my mind.

572
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:48,953
Wait!

573
00:40:49,033 --> 00:40:50,853
But I don't have much time.

574
00:40:50,933 --> 00:40:52,420
Just 10 minutes,

575
00:40:52,500 --> 00:40:55,120
don't feel so pressured.

576
00:40:55,200 --> 00:40:56,700
Alright.

577
00:41:05,066 --> 00:41:07,786
The Dom Perignon Limited Edition
you asked for, sir.

578
00:41:07,866 --> 00:41:10,066
Please serve it with
the cake later.

579
00:41:16,600 --> 00:41:19,300
A champagne's a must when
there's a reason to celebrate.

580
00:41:20,166 --> 00:41:21,233
Ms. Kim,

581
00:41:21,966 --> 00:41:23,120
congratulations!

582
00:41:23,200 --> 00:41:25,653
For being the only woman

583
00:41:25,733 --> 00:41:27,366
who'll receive my ordinary,
yet wholehearted confession.

584
00:41:31,466 --> 00:41:33,000
Looks like she'll be here soon.

585
00:41:44,900 --> 00:41:46,400
Huh? Morpheus!

586
00:41:49,733 --> 00:41:50,553
Wow.

587
00:41:50,633 --> 00:41:53,400
You were stunning before,
but even more so now.

588
00:41:54,500 --> 00:41:56,920
Looks like it's
an important date today?

589
00:41:57,000 --> 00:41:58,100
Sorry?

590
00:41:58,800 --> 00:42:00,533
Well, uh...

591
00:42:02,300 --> 00:42:04,920
I know this isn't something
we should discuss right here,

592
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:06,820
but I have no time, so...

593
00:42:06,900 --> 00:42:09,786
So, did you make up your mind?

594
00:42:09,866 --> 00:42:10,786
Yes.

595
00:42:10,866 --> 00:42:13,453
I thought I'd take your word
and give it a go.

596
00:42:13,533 --> 00:42:14,833
Really?

597
00:42:15,766 --> 00:42:17,386
Thank you so much!

598
00:42:17,466 --> 00:42:20,033
This is why I wanted to see you,
because I knew you'd be happy.

599
00:42:21,633 --> 00:42:22,700
Oh.

600
00:42:26,333 --> 00:42:27,333
(Once in a Lifetime)

601
00:42:27,333 --> 00:42:30,653
Huh? Isn't this your new book
that's coming up next week?

602
00:42:30,733 --> 00:42:31,853
It's for you.

603
00:42:31,933 --> 00:42:34,420
As token of our new partnership.

604
00:42:34,500 --> 00:42:36,100
Wow, thank you.

605
00:42:37,533 --> 00:42:39,653
If you open it, you'll have
more reasons to thank me.

606
00:42:39,733 --> 00:42:41,133
I even signed it for you.

607
00:42:43,433 --> 00:42:44,820
(A meeting that began
with coincidence)

608
00:42:44,900 --> 00:42:47,266
(might just be fate
Lee Sung-yeon)

609
00:42:54,600 --> 00:42:55,600
Mr. Lee!

610
00:43:01,266 --> 00:43:02,766
Mr. Lee, what was that for?

611
00:43:11,200 --> 00:43:13,453
Will you please explain
your actions just now?

612
00:43:13,533 --> 00:43:15,120
Why don't you do the explaining?

613
00:43:15,200 --> 00:43:16,766
About that situation just now.

614
00:43:17,900 --> 00:43:19,920
That was the Morpheus,
the novelist.

615
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:21,953
He came to say yes to
a proposal I made

616
00:43:22,033 --> 00:43:23,766
about a book concert at
our new art center.

617
00:43:24,833 --> 00:43:25,953
Since when did this
project go ahead?

618
00:43:26,033 --> 00:43:27,420
I mentioned it to you last time.

619
00:43:27,500 --> 00:43:28,953
About inviting
a bestselling author

620
00:43:29,033 --> 00:43:30,920
for our library's opening event.

621
00:43:31,000 --> 00:43:32,886
Is that the bestselling author

622
00:43:32,966 --> 00:43:33,986
- you were talking about?
- Yes.

623
00:43:34,066 --> 00:43:36,086
Then why did you
never report this to me?

624
00:43:36,166 --> 00:43:39,586
I thought it was meaningless to,
unless I was sure.

625
00:43:39,666 --> 00:43:40,886
Don't.

626
00:43:40,966 --> 00:43:41,886
Sorry?

627
00:43:41,966 --> 00:43:43,733
- But why...
- Just don't.

628
00:43:45,033 --> 00:43:46,353
May I ask why?

629
00:43:46,433 --> 00:43:49,066
Do I have to make you understand
every little thing?

630
00:43:50,166 --> 00:43:51,766
If I say no, it's a no.

631
00:44:02,233 --> 00:44:05,966
If this is nothing urgent,
then can I hear it next time?

632
00:44:08,500 --> 00:44:11,366
Fine. It wasn't anything
important anyway.

633
00:44:17,566 --> 00:44:19,200
Then I'll get going, sir.

634
00:44:47,633 --> 00:44:48,553
Are you alright?

635
00:44:48,633 --> 00:44:49,520
Sorry.

636
00:44:49,600 --> 00:44:51,033
I'm fine.

637
00:45:50,666 --> 00:45:53,000
I got my hopes up
and only hurt myself.

638
00:45:59,333 --> 00:46:00,353
What's this?

639
00:46:00,433 --> 00:46:01,966
You asking to see me?

640
00:46:06,533 --> 00:46:08,953
What are you planning?

641
00:46:09,033 --> 00:46:10,320
Just.

642
00:46:10,400 --> 00:46:13,586
Thought I should
contribute to the company.

643
00:46:13,666 --> 00:46:14,586
What?

644
00:46:14,666 --> 00:46:17,620
Apparently, me stepping forward
will be a great help.

645
00:46:17,700 --> 00:46:19,133
Mi-so said so.

646
00:46:25,433 --> 00:46:27,120
What's with that expression?

647
00:46:27,200 --> 00:46:28,620
Don't tell me...

648
00:46:28,700 --> 00:46:30,053
...Are you scared?

649
00:46:30,133 --> 00:46:34,020
That you'll lose Mi-so to me?

650
00:46:34,100 --> 00:46:36,020
No way.

651
00:46:36,100 --> 00:46:38,053
I don't think so.

652
00:46:38,133 --> 00:46:42,300
If you're so scared,
then should I just refuse?

653
00:46:44,566 --> 00:46:46,120
No.

654
00:46:46,200 --> 00:46:48,153
Go for it.

655
00:46:48,233 --> 00:46:49,186
What?

656
00:46:49,266 --> 00:46:50,286
It doesn't concern me,

657
00:46:50,366 --> 00:46:51,786
whether you do it or not.

658
00:46:51,866 --> 00:46:56,320
If you think this project will
influence the company or Ms. Kim

659
00:46:56,400 --> 00:46:58,133
in any way, then you're
overestimating yourself.

660
00:47:01,900 --> 00:47:03,533
Because you're not capable.

661
00:47:40,600 --> 00:47:41,853
Ms. Kim.

662
00:47:41,933 --> 00:47:45,300
I had my reason yesterday for
getting mad at you.

663
00:47:50,566 --> 00:47:51,653
Ms. Kim.

664
00:47:51,733 --> 00:47:53,453
If you apologize to me for
getting mad at me,

665
00:47:53,533 --> 00:47:55,200
then I might just forgive you.

666
00:47:57,333 --> 00:47:59,053
Ms. Kim.

667
00:47:59,133 --> 00:48:00,366
I'm sor...

668
00:48:09,533 --> 00:48:13,420
I might as well as
go escort her, right?

669
00:48:13,500 --> 00:48:15,353
Then let me wait outside.

670
00:48:15,433 --> 00:48:17,500
Young-joon, you!

671
00:48:21,866 --> 00:48:24,353
As token of our new partnership.

672
00:48:24,433 --> 00:48:25,853
Wow, thank you.

673
00:48:25,933 --> 00:48:27,786
If you open it, you'll have
more reasons to thank me.

674
00:48:27,866 --> 00:48:29,366
I even signed it for you.

675
00:48:44,166 --> 00:48:45,953
Mr. Lee is here.

676
00:48:46,033 --> 00:48:47,900
Good morning, Mr. Lee.

677
00:48:52,633 --> 00:48:53,986
He said good morning yesterday,

678
00:48:54,066 --> 00:48:55,353
so is today
a bad morning, or what?

679
00:48:55,433 --> 00:48:57,620
Right. He's a bit
different from last time.

680
00:48:57,700 --> 00:48:59,453
It's been a while,
you and your frivolous act.

681
00:48:59,533 --> 00:49:00,800
What is it this time?

682
00:49:02,633 --> 00:49:06,453
I got big news once again!

683
00:49:06,533 --> 00:49:08,733
Gather around, if you think
you can handle it.

684
00:49:09,266 --> 00:49:11,033
- Come on, gather around!
- Oh, what is it?

685
00:49:12,066 --> 00:49:12,986
Listen to this.

686
00:49:13,066 --> 00:49:16,000
For our library's opening event,

687
00:49:17,766 --> 00:49:20,120
we're going to have
a book concert with Morpheus!

688
00:49:20,200 --> 00:49:21,853
- What?
- No way.

689
00:49:21,933 --> 00:49:22,953
Just empty rumors again, huh?

690
00:49:23,033 --> 00:49:24,286
Why won't you believe me?

691
00:49:24,366 --> 00:49:25,453
- Geez.
- But I just...

692
00:49:25,533 --> 00:49:27,353
- Mr. Jung.
- Yes?

693
00:49:27,433 --> 00:49:29,320
Where did you hear that?

694
00:49:29,400 --> 00:49:30,786
From Marketing.

695
00:49:30,866 --> 00:49:33,420
Mr. Lee told them
himself, apparently.

696
00:49:33,500 --> 00:49:35,220
To prepare the
press release materials.

697
00:49:35,300 --> 00:49:36,400
What?

698
00:49:58,066 --> 00:49:59,920
The book concert with Morpheus.

699
00:50:00,000 --> 00:50:02,300
Is it true you gave a go on it?

700
00:50:14,100 --> 00:50:15,266
It's true.

701
00:50:16,300 --> 00:50:18,486
May I ask why, all of a sudden,

702
00:50:18,566 --> 00:50:21,466
when you said it's a firm no
only yesterday?

703
00:50:24,100 --> 00:50:25,386
Oh,

704
00:50:25,466 --> 00:50:28,186
but there's no reason for you to
explain every detail for me.

705
00:50:28,266 --> 00:50:29,500
Isn't that right?

706
00:50:34,033 --> 00:50:35,800
Then please don't
cross the line from now on.

707
00:50:38,300 --> 00:50:39,653
To be honest, I...

708
00:50:39,733 --> 00:50:41,153
I misunderstood some things.

709
00:50:41,233 --> 00:50:42,786
After the marriage proposals
and asking me out,

710
00:50:42,866 --> 00:50:45,133
and your sudden change of
attitude, I thought maybe...

711
00:50:46,333 --> 00:50:47,933
...That you meant it.

712
00:50:50,666 --> 00:50:51,920
Ms. Kim...

713
00:50:52,000 --> 00:50:53,266
Don't...

714
00:50:54,466 --> 00:50:56,033
...Shake me up again.

715
00:51:15,300 --> 00:51:17,620
Exactly!

716
00:51:17,700 --> 00:51:19,333
It's Mr. Koh Gui-nam!

717
00:51:20,066 --> 00:51:21,286
Oh no.

718
00:51:21,366 --> 00:51:23,486
I forgot to bring that
button from yesterday.

719
00:51:23,566 --> 00:51:25,820
You need to
give it back to him, quick!

720
00:51:25,900 --> 00:51:27,820
That's his only suit,
so it'll be hard for him.

721
00:51:27,900 --> 00:51:29,353
Ji-ah, aren't you obstinate?

722
00:51:29,433 --> 00:51:31,086
Why do you keep on saying
he has just one suit?

723
00:51:31,166 --> 00:51:33,800
Because there are clear evidence...

724
00:51:34,833 --> 00:51:36,986
How about a bet?

725
00:51:37,066 --> 00:51:38,520
Since he lost that
button yesterday,

726
00:51:38,600 --> 00:51:41,120
I bet his jacket is
missing a button.

727
00:51:41,200 --> 00:51:41,953
Why?

728
00:51:42,033 --> 00:51:43,720
Because he only has one suit.

729
00:51:43,800 --> 00:51:45,700
I think I should clear that up.

730
00:51:46,766 --> 00:51:48,300
Hello.

731
00:51:49,666 --> 00:51:50,720
Have a look.

732
00:51:50,800 --> 00:51:53,633
See if there's
a button that's missing.

733
00:51:54,333 --> 00:51:55,020
Uh...

734
00:51:55,100 --> 00:51:56,353
Alright, here's four.

735
00:51:56,433 --> 00:51:58,686
And here's four.
And here's two.

736
00:51:58,766 --> 00:52:01,220
And one each,
on the inner pockets.

737
00:52:01,300 --> 00:52:02,300
And...

738
00:52:03,966 --> 00:52:05,533
I even have spare buttons!

739
00:52:06,233 --> 00:52:08,186
I have all my buttons.

740
00:52:08,266 --> 00:52:10,620
I'm sorry. I made a big mistake...

741
00:52:10,700 --> 00:52:12,086
How about I buy you a drink to
apologize for my colleague?

742
00:52:12,166 --> 00:52:13,533
It's alright.

743
00:52:13,800 --> 00:52:16,020
But please refrain from

744
00:52:16,100 --> 00:52:17,733
making up rumors from now on.

745
00:52:19,933 --> 00:52:20,820
I'm sorry.

746
00:52:20,900 --> 00:52:22,453
Instead of rumors,
how about just beer?

747
00:52:22,533 --> 00:52:24,520
If you're not into beer,
then soju?

748
00:52:24,600 --> 00:52:26,353
Or makgeolli?

749
00:52:26,433 --> 00:52:27,553
Ugh!

750
00:52:27,633 --> 00:52:28,786
What did I tell you?

751
00:52:28,866 --> 00:52:30,666
I told you to
stop playing detective!

752
00:52:52,066 --> 00:52:54,653
Looks like she's quite mad.

753
00:52:54,733 --> 00:52:56,066
What should I do?

754
00:53:22,333 --> 00:53:23,553
Ugh, my head.

755
00:53:23,633 --> 00:53:25,666
I have a headache...

756
00:53:27,400 --> 00:53:28,320
Hello, Dr. Park?

757
00:53:28,400 --> 00:53:30,320
Mr. Lee has a headache.

758
00:53:30,400 --> 00:53:31,786
Can he come in for
an appointment at 10...

759
00:53:31,866 --> 00:53:33,253
No, it's not that bad.

760
00:53:33,333 --> 00:53:34,986
He says it's not that bad.

761
00:53:35,066 --> 00:53:36,433
Yes, doctor.

762
00:54:13,433 --> 00:54:15,686
I sent the opening speech for
the welfare center opening

763
00:54:15,766 --> 00:54:18,033
to your e-mail. Please check.

764
00:54:21,833 --> 00:54:24,866
It seems my tie's loose...

765
00:54:46,266 --> 00:54:47,333
Ms. Kim!

766
00:54:49,266 --> 00:54:52,820
I have big news, once again!

767
00:54:52,900 --> 00:54:53,853
What?

768
00:54:53,933 --> 00:54:58,366
While talking with Marketing about
the book concert with Morpheus,

769
00:54:59,366 --> 00:55:01,000
I heard something unbelievable!

770
00:55:02,066 --> 00:55:03,166
Ms. Kim.

771
00:55:04,566 --> 00:55:07,053
Do you think you'll be
able to handle it?

772
00:55:07,133 --> 00:55:08,253
I'll try my best.

773
00:55:08,333 --> 00:55:09,920
Don't be shocked.

774
00:55:10,000 --> 00:55:11,953
But Morpheus is...

775
00:55:12,033 --> 00:55:13,600
...He's Mr. Lee's older brother!

776
00:55:16,633 --> 00:55:17,800
What?

777
00:55:18,166 --> 00:55:19,120
Is this true?

778
00:55:19,200 --> 00:55:21,753
Yes, it's true!
Of course it's the truth!

779
00:55:21,833 --> 00:55:24,653
Morpheus was the elder son of
Yumyung Group...

780
00:55:24,733 --> 00:55:29,600
Now isn't that big news?

781
00:55:31,666 --> 00:55:36,020
Well, I remembered you
asking me about Mr. Lee's brother,

782
00:55:36,100 --> 00:55:38,666
so I ran here to tell you!

783
00:55:42,566 --> 00:55:45,766
The eldest son that's been missing
has finally appeared...

784
00:55:46,833 --> 00:55:49,686
Maybe that means
looks like they'll be

785
00:55:49,766 --> 00:55:52,600
some shifts to the
company succession plans?

786
00:56:02,333 --> 00:56:04,453
I quarreled a lot
with my brother's friends.

787
00:56:04,533 --> 00:56:07,986
They'd pick on me,
saying I was an arrogant brat.

788
00:56:08,066 --> 00:56:11,953
But at least you were with
your brother, thank goodness!

789
00:56:12,033 --> 00:56:13,300
No.

790
00:56:14,033 --> 00:56:15,386
He was worse.

791
00:56:15,466 --> 00:56:17,700
A total jerk, he was.

792
00:56:18,833 --> 00:56:21,533
It seemed like things weren't
good with his brother.

793
00:56:23,133 --> 00:56:24,453
What?

794
00:56:24,533 --> 00:56:26,733
How to say sorry?

795
00:56:29,100 --> 00:56:29,953
How is that so hard?

796
00:56:30,033 --> 00:56:32,253
Just say, 'Sorry!'

797
00:56:32,333 --> 00:56:35,033
Do you know what
'sorry' is in Spanish?

798
00:56:37,900 --> 00:56:39,486
It's 'Lo Siento.'

799
00:56:39,566 --> 00:56:40,953
Try saying it.

800
00:56:41,033 --> 00:56:43,033
Lo... Lo Si...

801
00:56:44,033 --> 00:56:45,666
Oh, forget it.

802
00:56:46,433 --> 00:56:47,820
Doesn't really
roll off your tongue, right?

803
00:56:47,900 --> 00:56:50,286
Because you've never said it.

804
00:56:50,366 --> 00:56:52,386
That's what the word
'sorry' is like to me.

805
00:56:52,466 --> 00:56:54,553
I've never said it.

806
